The paper also uses large-scale data analysis, which suggests the possibility of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper analyzes the impact of mentorship on scientific papers, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
